docs/*.tar.gz
publish/
# CLST-2: WASM build output mirrored from src/NINA.Polaris.Wasm/bin/.../AppBundle/
# Rebuild with deploy/build-wasm.ps1.
src/NINA.Polaris/wwwroot/js/wasm/
build-output/

# Runtime capture output — recorded by the user's local session,
# never belongs in the repo.
src/NINA.Polaris/planetary/
src/NINA.Polaris/snaps/
src/NINA.Polaris/lights/
src/NINA.Polaris/calibration/
src/NINA.Polaris/calibrated/
src/NINA.Polaris/integrated/
src/NINA.Polaris/processed/

# SWE-3: Stellarium Web HiPS skydata. The compact test-skydata
# (~4.6MB total — HiPS Norder0/1 tile pyramids for stars + DSOs
# + Milky Way survey + Moon + Sun + IAU constellations + DE441
# planet ephemeris) ships in-repo at
# src/NINA.Polaris/wwwroot/sky/data/skydata/ so the sky map works
# offline out of the box. The earlier idea of a "fetch from
# CloudFront" script was abandoned — the CloudFront URL we
# discovered turned out to be the stellarium-web.org SPA hosting
# bucket, not a HiPS data mirror, and CloudFront does not serve
# directory indices crawlers can walk anyway. The committed copy
# comes from external/stellarium-web-engine/apps/test-skydata/
# under AGPL — copy is verbatim from the submodule.

# GX-12j: bundled GraXpert ONNX models live under
# wwwroot/graxpert/models/ so OnnxModelRegistry picks them up
# automatically. The .onnx files are huge (1.5 GB total) and the
# model license (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0) forbids us from redistributing
# them. The README + .gitkeep in that directory ARE tracked so the
# directory structure survives a clone — operators drop their own
# models in matching the GraXpert layout (see README.md).
src/NINA.Polaris/wwwroot/graxpert/models/**/*.onnx
nanobanana-output/

# CCALB-3a: bundled APASS DR9 star catalog used by Photometric
# Color Calibration (PCC). The .db file is ~600 MB at the default
# Vmag <= 13 cap (5.3M stars + R*tree index). Built by
# scripts/download-apass.py via VizieR TAP (II/336/apass9). Skipped
# from the repo because (a) size, (b) catalog data is third-party
# with its own attribution requirement (CC-BY). Polaris's publish
# output picks it up via the default wwwroot/** rule.
src/NINA.Polaris/wwwroot/catalogs/apass/*.db

# Real-capture fixture used by the E2E pipeline test
# (tests/NINA.Polaris.Test/E2E/RealDataPipelineTests.cs). ~19 GB
# of mono SHO + OSC sessions captured locally; not redistributed
# in the repo. Drop your own NINA-format captures here (any
# subfolder layout works, the rescan walks recursively and reads
# IMAGETYP / FILTER / OBJECT from FITS headers) to run the
# fixture via `dotnet test --filter "Category=E2E"`.
test_data/
scripts/.apass-cache/
/external_tools
